values:
I hope the love in my heart right now&nbsp;never tarnishes or thins or gets annoying.&nbsp;
I wish I could give what I feel like a gift, a piece of the sky from my pocket...

I really feel like most people deserve so much better.&nbsp;

On that note,&nbsp; I feel like I owe an apology to someone, but I'm afraid I'll never be able to show her how sincere I am.&nbsp; I'm afraid she won't listen because I am the enemy.&nbsp;&nbsp; Girls don't let go of things like that. They know who you are, and they'll always hate you.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

It is a shame because I now realize we are so much alike, that, in some other world where we met at a different time and place, we are best friends.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;
I want to make restitution.

Her thoughts are so candid...I love reading what she has to say.

She doesn't know that I know.&nbsp; If she did know, she might freak out.&nbsp;&nbsp; Then again she might not, but its...weird.&nbsp;And I'm weird. really really weird...
And even if all things went well,&nbsp; it would be awkward wouldn't it?&nbsp; After what I put her through?&nbsp; Because of who we know?&nbsp; Because of how we met?&nbsp; It just kinda sucks that I messed things up like that.&nbsp;

Sometimes I wish all the things that were ever said about me were written down in a book, and that from time to time, I could sample a page.
She will probably never know that I read entry after entry of her life.&nbsp; That I stop and think about her ideas.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Its like looking down at people below you from the balcony.&nbsp; Thats my favorite.&nbsp; Those people have no clue they are being watched and pondered upon by a stranger.&nbsp;&nbsp; They have no idea that in some small way, without doing ANYTHING, they make an impression on someone they will never ever ever interact with.&nbsp;&nbsp; I love thinking about stuff like this.&nbsp; It blows my mind.&nbsp; The human connection.&nbsp;
